        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 14 at 4:06PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 406 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Big Otter, or 15 miles west of Sutton, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Sutton, Gassaway, Big Otter, Burnsville, Flatwoods, Shock, Nebo,
Frametown, Strange Creek, Wilsie, Servia, Rosedale, Exchange,
Heaters, Ivydale, Nicut, Cedarville, Chloe, and Falls Mills.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 79 between mile markers 39 and 79.
Route 19 near mile marker 68.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

This storm may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
